The total variation of a complex measure obtained from the Riesz-Markov-Kakutani representation theorem is equal to the norm of the continuous linear functional from which it is derived. Given that `cfc_toComplexMeasure` is defined using a bounded linear functional whose norm is bounded by `‖x‖ * ‖y‖`, the variation of the resulting measure over the entire set `Set.univ` is likewise bounded.

```lean
/-- The complex measure `E_{a, x,y}` has the total variation bounded by `‖x‖ * ‖y‖`.
Rudin "Real and complex analysis" Theorem 6.19 (2), combined with the bound by
`cfc_toLinearFunctional_bound`.-/
lemma cfc_variation_toComplexMeasure_bounded (x y : H) :
    (cfc_toComplexMeasure ha x y).variation Set.univ ≤ ‖x‖ₑ * ‖y‖ₑ := by
  rw [cfc_toComplexMeasure]
  refine (ComplexRMK.variation_rieszMeasure_le _ Set.univ).trans ?_
  simp only [ContinuousLinearMap.nnnorm_comp_le, LinearIsometryEquiv.nnnorm_toContinuousLinearMap,
    ENNReal.coe_mul, ENNReal.coe_one, mul_one]
  exact_mod_cast cfc_toLinearFunctional_bound ha x y
```
